The paper discusses the limitations of current network security systems and proposes a new direction for cybersecurity development inspired by nature. This aligns with the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of bio-inspired approaches, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The proposed framework for mapping biological security systems to their cyber analogies involves systematic research and development, which aligns with the sub-categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
